column16: G = Glass eel/elver of zero age
Y = young yellow eel recruits - or bootlace
GY= all recruits mixed and no age or stage data
Shoreline = colections using scopp net or tweezers
Plankton net = off bridge netting of incoming glass eels on rising tide.
SRP = release pond trap at Mill Race - eels migrating upstream into frshwater
Main = old main elver traps, destroyed in 1989 - eels migrating upstream into freshwater - about 50m upstream of SRP
SL - Salmon Leap upstream migrating into freshwater, equivalent to SRP&Main - sometimes combined with Main
